{"title": "The Seven Mysteries", "content": "Apparently, mysterious phenomena come in groups of seven.\n\nWhy? Well, that's a mystery. There's probably six more.\n\nAn urban legend especially common in a Japanese school setting, these tend to be awkwardly brought up during summer episodes, where mysterious legends are attributed to a not-particularly-old place. Nearly always end up being complete horsehockey, except for perhaps the last one. Common themes include voices in an empty room, faces in a wall, staircases with more steps going up than coming down, and other variously spooky and paranormal things.\n\nNote that this is not the same as there being seven Objects of Power, or other Numerological Motifs associated with the number seven - it's specifically the Japanese cultural phenomenon of places with seven unrelated but strange and mysterious things that happen in an otherwise normal place.\n\nA common punchline is for the seventh mystery to be that there are only six mysteries.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSevenMysteries", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Doraemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/UruseiYatsura", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/StrawberryPanic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Mahoromatic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TheKindaichiCaseFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MaiHiME", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/RanmaOneHalf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MythicalDetectiveLokiRagnarok", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ToeiAnimation", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/Kanon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/UtaKata", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DirtyPairFlash", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FairyMusketeers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Kekkaishi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MariaHolic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AirGear", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/SeitokaiNoIchizon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/HiganbanaNoSakuYoruNi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DuskMaidenOfAmnesia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SgtFrog", "/